UltraJSON is a fast and extendable JSON encoder and decoder written in pure C

Python bindings are available as the module ujson with the methods decode and encode


Preliminary benchmarks:

Python 2.6.6 (r266:84297, Aug 24 2010, 18:46:32) [MSC v.1500 32 bit (Intel)]
Host Name:                 FORD
OS Version:                6.1.7601 Service Pack 1 Build 7601
System Type:               x64-based PC
Processor(s):              1 Processor(s) Installed.
                           [01]: Intel64 Family 6 Model 23 Stepping 7 GenuineIntel ~1983 Mhz
Total Physical Memory:     8 191 MB


Encoding:
ujson encode      : 10288.64358 calls/sec
simplejson encode : 2516.58023 calls/sec
cjson encode      : 2043.66286 calls/sec
json encode       : 277.71662 calls/sec

Decoding:
ujson decode      : 7024.01151 calls/sec
cjson decode      : 3583.00350 calls/sec
simplejson decode : 3540.54171 calls/sec
json decode       : 118.00904 calls/sec

See (python/benchmark.py) for further information.

NOTE: These benchmarks are preliminary! 

